'From Squeak2.9alpha of 13 June 2000 [latest update: #2968] on 7 November 2000 at 6:58:57 pm'!"Change Set:		DragFix-arDate:			7 November 2000Author:			Andreas RaabQuick fix for multi selection list morphs."!!PluggableListMorphOfMany methodsFor: 'as yet unclassified' stamp: 'ar 11/7/2000 18:57'!mouseDown: event onItem: aMorph	| index oldIndex oldVal |	event yellowButtonPressed ifTrue: [^ self yellowButtonActivity: event shiftPressed].	model okToChange ifFalse: [^ self].  "No change if model is locked"	index _ scroller submorphs indexOf: aMorph.	index = 0 ifTrue: [^ self  "minimize chance of selecting with a pane border drag"].	"Set meaning for subsequent dragging of selection"	dragOnOrOff _ (model listSelectionAt: index) not.	oldIndex _ self getCurrentSelectionIndex.	oldIndex ~= 0 ifTrue: [oldVal _ model listSelectionAt: oldIndex].	"Set or clear new primary selection (listIndex)"	dragOnOrOff		ifTrue: [self setSelectedMorph: aMorph]		ifFalse: [self setSelectedMorph: nil].	"Need to restore the old one, due to how model works, and set new one."	oldIndex ~= 0 ifTrue: [model listSelectionAt: oldIndex put: oldVal].	model listSelectionAt: index put: dragOnOrOff.	event hand releaseMouseFocus: aMorph.	aMorph changed! !